The U.S. will host the "Summit for Democracy" on December 9 and 10, having already unilaterally decided who is eligible for attendance and who is not. However, democracy is not a patent owned by any single country, but rather a value shared by all mankind. Touting democracy is not simply a matter of trite slogans, but rather of results on the ground. Credits: Editor: Yuan Xin Senior producer: Wei Wei Managing director: Mei Yan (To submit cartoons and share story ideas or feedback on our cartoon page, please contact us at cartoon_opinions@cgtn.com)